class Solution {
public:
    int rand10() {
        int x;
        do {
            x = (rand7() - 1) * 7 + (rand7() - 1);
        } while (x >= 40);
        return (x % 10) + 1;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) expected
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses rejection sampling on a 7×7 grid (49 outcomes) to map 40 of them uniformly to 0-39, then mod 10 to get 1-10. Expected calls to rand7() is 2.45, minimizing waste.

